'''Marcion''' is [[Coptic language|Coptic]]–[[English language|English]]/[[Czech language|Czech]] [[dictionary]] related to [[Walter Ewing Crum|Crum]]'s coptic dictionary,<ref>{{cite web|last=Konvicka|first=Milan|title=Coptic dictionary|url=http://marcion.sourceforge.net/dictionary/coptic.html|work=Marcion - software to study the Gnostic scriptures|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref>  written in [[C++]],<ref name=sf-project>{{cite web|title=Marcion|url=http://sourceforge.net/projects/marcion/|work=SourceForge|accessdate=21 June 2013|author=vagrantos|date=10 June 2013}}</ref>  based on [[MySQL]],{{Citation needed|date=June 2013}} with [[Qt (framework)|Qt]] GUI.<ref name=sf-project />  Contains many coptic texts, grammars, Greek texts,<ref>{{cite web|last=Konvicka|first=Milan|title=texts|url=http://marcion.sourceforge.net/#texts|work=Marcion - software to study the Gnostic scriptures|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref> [[A Greek–English Lexicon|Liddell–Scott Greek–English lexicon]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Konvicka|first=Milan|title=Greek dictionary|url=http://marcion.sourceforge.net/dictionary/ancient-greek.html|work=Marcion - software to study the Gnostic scriptures|accessdate=21 June 2013}}</ref> and others. Can be used as a [[Bible study (Christian)|bible study]] tool. Marcion is [[free software]] released under the [[GNU GPL]].

